cs.PL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.LG

This paper discusses the implementation and applications of Tabled Logic Programming (TLP) in XSB Prolog, which is a subfield of logic programming. Therefore, cs.PL (Programming Languages) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of TLP in program analysis and querying over the semantic web, which are related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The discussion of how XSB supports tabling with dynamically changing code and in a multi-threaded environment is related to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper's focus on efficiency and optimization may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
